flowchart TD
    A[Incoming Client Request] --> B[FastAPI Gateway]
    B --> C[Get Healthy and Enabled Backends]

    C --> D{Any Eligible Backend?}
    D -- No --> E[Return 503 Service Unavailable]
    D -- Yes --> F[Read active_requests and weight]

    F --> G[Calculate active_requests divided by weight]
    G --> H[Find Lowest Normalized Load]

    H --> I{Multiple Backends Tied?}
    I -- Yes --> J[Use Fair Round Robin Tie Break]
    I -- No --> K[Select Lowest-Load Backend]
    J --> K

    K --> L[Atomically Increment active_requests]
    L --> M[Forward Request to Backend]

    M --> N{Request Successful?}
    N -- Yes --> O[Stream Response to Client]
    N -- No --> P{Retry Available?}

    P -- Yes --> Q[Exclude Failed Backend]
    Q --> C

    P -- No --> R[Return Final Error]

    O --> S[Response Stream Finished]
    R --> S

    S --> T[Decrement active_requests]
    T --> U[Update Latency and Error Metrics]
    U --> V[Persist Request History in Supabase]
    V --> W[Publish SSE Lifecycle Event]
    W --> X[Update Live API Request Topology]